Title:     The best word yet.
             (evaluation of Microsoft Word for Windows 6.0) (includes
             related articles on features and comparison to version 2.0)
Author:    Finnie, Scot
           Bott, Ed


Abstract:  Microsoft's $495 Word for Windows 6.0 is an enormous
           improvement over the previous 2.0 version and now sets the
           standard for word processor usability.  Word for Windows 6.0
           does not offer an array of new features, instead focusing on
           enormous usability improvements and shortcuts to features that
           have long existed in the program.  This version is more
           advanced than any other version of Word and beats the
           competition until it catches up.  The biggest new feature in
           6.0 is push-button power to complex tasks.  AutoFormat,
           AutoCorrect and other automated features greatly enhance this
           package.  Smaller additions include multiple toolbars,
           redesigned dialog boxes, a multiple document interface and a
           redone ruler and status bar.  Word also has finally received
           Microsoft's Wizard online help assistants.
