Why Word 6.0 for Windows Is a Wiz

30 great reasons to upgrade.

1.  Document: Minimizing You can minimize documents into icons inside
Word's application window with support for the multiple document
interface (MDI).

2.  Multilevel undo: You get "uh-oh" control, thanks to 100 (or more)
levels of Undo and Redo.

3.  Improved compatibility: Look for dozens of WordPerfect compatibility
features, including improved document conversion and animated demos.

4.  Improved background printing: Get back to work literally moments
after you click on the Print icon with Word's background printing.

5.  Editable preview: You can edit in Print Preview mode, and Word gives
you an up-close look at full pages or it shows thumbnails of an entire
document.

6.  Workgroup features: You can take advantage of vastly improved
workgroup features, including extensive color-revision marking and
merging, plus routing that works in conjunction with your e-mail
software.

7.  Right-mouse support: You get context-sensitive dialog boxes that pop
up with a click of the right-mouse button when you click on toolbars,
document areas, and other "hot" locations.

8.  Enhanced layout mode: Get used to working in Page Layout View and
enjoying it because Word scrolls more quickly and smoothly than before,
shows frame anchors, and displays headers and footers.

9.  AUTOCORRECT: No more typos! With AutoCorrect, you can customize Word
to fix misspellings, mistypings, or to add the correct accents to foreign
words--all on the fly.

10.  Labels and envelopes: You can stop hand-writing your envelopes and
achieve that consistent, professional look--configure and print your
special forms much easier thanks to Word's significantly enhanced label
and envelope print settings.

11.  FORMAT PAINTER: You can copy character formatting from one piece of
text to another.  Just click on the text to copy, click on the Format
Painter icon, then drag the new cursor to "paint" the selected text with
the new format.

12.  TOOLTIPS: You see informative text labels that pop up automatically
when you hold your cursor over an icon for a few seconds, so you'll never
forget what a particular toolbar button does.

13.  Organizer: Copy styles, macros, toolbars, and AutoText (Glossary)
items among Word files, and share customizations among documents and
co-workers.

14.  UNINSTALL: Zap all traces of the program or selectively remove one
component of a program at a time with Word's complete uninstall routine.

15.  File open: You can open a group of files simultaneously with the
improved open feature.

16.  MACROS: You can record macros quicker than ever, with easy-to-use
dialog boxes and toolbar functions.

17.  Toolbars: Word ships with 13 predefined toolbars, complete with
color icons.  You can customize and configure toolbars in a variety of
shapes that you can place almost anywhere on the screen.

18.  THREE-KEY SORTS: You can easily perform three-key sorts with Word's
nearly perfect sorting capabilities.

19.  IMPROVED MERGE: Your mail tasks are easier with Word's top-notch
mail merge, which now includes extensive support for external databases,
including links to Microsoft Access.

20.  WIZARDS: In no time at all, you can easily design fax cover sheets,
calendars, agendas, and more with Word's nine Wizard templates.

21.  LAYOUT: Features It's not QuarkXPress, but Word's rich and intuitive
desktop publishing features include easy frame-handling controls, visible
anchors, and options such as automated caption creation.

22.  BETTER RULER: You can drag both left indent settings in one smooth
motion with the handle on Word's ruler.  There's also an optional
vertical ruler.

23.  STATUS BAR: With the status bar at the bottom of the screen, you can
double-click to open WordPerfect Help, launch the Macro Recorder, and
lock in Extend Selection mode, which lets you select text as you move the
cursor.

24.  HORIZONTAL SCROLL BAR: Word's scroll bar gives you built-in buttons
for Normal, Outline, and Page Layout views.

25.  Cursor in context: Word's chameleon-like I-bar text cursor now fully
adapts to reflect the text it's placed in, changing in response to font
attributes, including point size, superscript, and subscript.

26.  Insert symbols: You can insert multiple symbols without closing

automatically, and the Symbols dialog box includes a separate list of
common special characters like trademark and copyright symbols.

27.  COLUMNS: With Word'simproved Columns dialog box, you can easily
configure variable-width columns.  You'll also find five preset column
types, each one just a click away.

28.  Accessible fonts: You can check out the fonts you've used most
recently. They appear at the top of the drop-down font list on the
Formatting toolbar.

29.  LARGE DOCUMENTS: Write your own encyclopedia! Word 6.0 handles
documents up to 32MB in size, where Word 2.0 quit at a mere 16MB.

30.  FIND FILES: You can perform lightning-fast searches with the
overhauled Find File facility that not only caches searches but also
works in the background.

